One of the ways to evaluate whether a given policy/system can be beneficial for a firm is by solving for its net present value. Basically, the net present value compares the revenue and cost of the policy which means that it shows whether the policy will be profitable or not.

The net present value can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Net present value}&=\text{Total revenue}-\text{Total cost}
\end{aligned}$$
